# Project Constitution

> Governing principles, values, and development guidelines for chatbot-sdd.

## Mission & Vision

_What problem does this project solve? What is the long-term vision?_

## Core Values

- _e.g., Simplicity over complexity_
- _e.g., Security by design_
- _e.g., Testable by default_
- _e.g., Iterate fast, validate often_

## Architecture Principles

- _e.g., OpenAPI-first: spec drives all interfaces_
- _e.g., Stateless backend, state managed by client/database_
- _e.g., Streaming-first for AI responses_
- _e.g., Separate concerns: API layer, service layer, data layer_

## Tech Stack Rationale

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Backend | FastAPI + Python | Async-native, OpenAPI generation, strong typing via Pydantic |
| Frontend | React + TypeScript | Component ecosystem, type safety, SSE support |
| AI SDK | Databricks SDK | Primary AI provider integration |
| Auth | JWT + python-jose | Stateless, simple, standard |
| Spec | OpenAPI 3.1 | Contract-first, language-agnostic |
| Database | _(TBD)_ | |

## Code Standards

- Type hints everywhere (Python: mypy strict, TS: strict mode)
- Imports: stdlib → third-party → local (grouped, sorted)
- Naming: `snake_case` (Python), `camelCase` (TS), `PascalCase` (classes/components)
- Max line length: 100
- Docstrings: Google style for public APIs only
- No commented-out code — delete it

## Testing Philosophy

- Contract tests validate OpenAPI compliance
- Unit tests for services/utils
- Integration tests for API routes
- AI evaluation suite for chatbot quality (golden dataset)
- Coverage target: >80%

## Development Workflow

- Branch: `main` (stable), feature branches off `main`
- PRs require passing CI + review
- Semantic commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `chore:`
- spec changes go through `speckit.specify` → `speckit.plan` → implementation
- ADRs for significant decisions

